 H2 becomes far\nmore abundant than H and the O/H ratio grows, the reactivity of O atoms on\ngrains is such that O becomes one of the dominant reactive partners together\nwith H.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 24 Feb 2014 15:31:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 5 Jun 2014 10:11:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-06-06"}
